{
  "texts": [
    "Especially in this era where online-and hybrid learning is prevalent, AI can leverage the wealth of information generated from online learning platforms such as Moodle (Jin, 2012).",
    "This capability informs not only students about how they did but also instructors about patterns of students' learning (e.g., distribution of quiz scores) to inform their instruction planning.The mentioned innovation is driven primarily by students' data, such as students' engagement with course materials through a learning management system and their assessment scores (Bulut et al., 2023; Yildirim-Erbasli et al., 2023).",
    "For this reason, instructors and researchers must ensure that all information is given with consent and that no misuse occurs (Stahl & Karger, 2016).",
    "Schools and academic institutions should implement data privacy measures, educating students about their data rights and maintaining transparency about how and why their data is being used (Lin & Kifer, 2015; Stahl & Karger, 2016).",
    "Potential misuse of students' data in the feedback process includes data misinterpretation, inconsistent data definition (i.e., comparing different kinds of data), poor result visualization (i.e., choice of graphs, texts, and colors) (Webber, 2019)."
  ]
}